overview: New Yorker Ben Phillips and mysterious Léo Hoffmann are strangers who are summoned to Paris by a mutual acquaintance.  Upon arrival, they meet and soon find themselves tangled in a complex mystery.
title: Merry-Go-Round

overview: A good-natured, wacko comedy with a strange little breeze of the avant-garde.
title: King of LA

overview: Hanai Sota is 22-years-old and a university student in the veterinary department. Since he was little, he has always loved animals. His apartment is full of animals that needed help. One day, Hanai Sota saves a dog that was being used in experiments. To save more of the animals, he sets up the "Inubu" club. His friend Shibasaki Ryosuke, among other people, joins the group. Shibasaki Ryosuke also loves dogs and is a student in the same veterinary department as Hanai Sota. They work hard to protect the animals. 16 years later, a report comes out. The report is about Hanai Sota, who was arrested.
title: Inubu: The Dog Club

overview: In Nightwatch - Demons are Forever, Emma, a medical student, takes on a nightwatch job in the forensic department. And it is no coincidence. Since the fatal night - 30 years earlier, when psychopathic inspector Wörmer almost killed Emma's parents, who were saved at the very last minute by their friend Jens, her family has been haunted by this horrific memory. Her mother Kalinka, actually committed suicide when Emma was 10 and her father Martin is still the shadow of himself. The young woman decides to investigate what happened in her parents’ past. Upon meeting with Wörmer, Emma wakes him from his coma, and unintentionally initiates a bloody revenge on all of those who sealed Wörmer’s destiny.
title: Nightwatch: Demons Are Forever

overview: Nusa Antara (The Nusantara) is an animated documentary short film, which records the ideas and dialogues of each director involved (film director, animation director, sound director) related to childhood memories, and/or past memories about what it means to live and live in Indonesia.  Indonesia, an archipelagic country, highlighting illegal logging, romance, COVID-19, and life in the countryside.
title: Nusa Antara

overview: Inspired from a shockingly true incident of Hate and Revenge. The film is an investigative thriller that explores the mind-set of a criminal hiding in plain sight. A newly married couple receives a gift box five days after their wedding, their happiness turns short lived when the gift turns out to be a bomb that kills the husband and his grandmother and seriously injuring the wife. A massive investigation begins to find the killer.
tagline: A tribute to the intelligence of Odisha police
title: Mind Game

overview: God answers unscripted questions on live TV as billions of onlookers watch in awe.
title: God 2.0

overview: Taipei City in 2022 is a dynamic, exciting and vibrant city! “Huannan” is a traditional market that sits on the triangle formed by the Tamsui River and Xindian River. It has served as the major food and beverage market for the entire capital city for over 55 years. Our tale is set in 1991.As with the unique market, secret ingredients are thrown into the story of the Huannan Gang. At that time, everyone knew that the gang was of three boys and one girl, but no one knew that the youngest member was from 2022...
title: The Time of Huan Nan

overview: To Rizoo, 8—who’s recently moved back to Tehran from California—the world is a magical place. But when she must take a class portrait, her world suddenly becomes very complicated. Does she wear the traditional head-scarf, which all girls over the age of 9 must wear—or not? Seemingly everyone has an opinion. We witness Rizoo navigate the challenges of growing up a California girl in modern Iran. She may be small in size, but her spirit is big enough to change the world.
title: Rizoo

overview: After many years together, a couple decides to have a baby. Throughout their relentless efforts, the partners try to maintain their love and unity. MAKING BABIES is a minimalist comedy drama that takes a bittersweet look at a couple’s life, with its doubts, its challenges and its resilience.
title: Making Babies

overview: Have you ever wondered if you could be a hero? Would you hide an entire family? Who would hide you if YOU needed to be hidden? I am the daughter of Holocaust survivor and the questions I ask myself all the time are: "would I be here if my mother hadn't been hidden?" and "who else helped my mother and her siblings survive?"
title: UnBroken

overview: Alison remains notoriously anonymous when critiquing restaurants for the Chicago Tribune because she never wants to be treated differently than an ordinary customer. But when she accidentally goes viral for trashing a new restaurant, her editor insists she make amends by going undercover as a prep cook for the chef she maligned.
title: With Love, Your Sweetly Salted

overview: After saving her town from a psychotic killer, Winnie Carruthers' life is less than wonderful. When she wishes she'd never been born, she finds herself in a nightmare parallel universe where without her, things could be much, much worse.
tagline: Every time a bell rings an angel gets to KILL!
title: It's a Wonderful Knife

overview: After being compassionately released from prison, a terminally ill man navigates through his remaining days trying to reconnect with his estranged son.
tagline: Freedom is the last step before eternity
title: Charles Sloan

overview: Plot Unavailable.
title: Kaaincha Maali

overview: Green is a professor in a long-term relationship with her lesbian partner. Failing at preparing the deposit for the house and Green being laid off for helping her homosexual colleague, the only option they can choose is to move in with Green’s mother. As their awkward stay prolongs, the mother drives all her energy into her job as a caregiver.
title: Concerning My Daughter

overview: Film director Kabir comes to Varanasi, the most sacred site of Hinduism that has existed since BC, with a camera. Kabir begins to photograph two people: Durga, one of the workers at the crematorium on the banks of the Ganges, and Amman, who has come to Varanasi to await death in order to break the chain of reincarnation.
title: The Spark

overview: A young refugee tries to make a living delivering food by bike and becomes a target for Zurich's most dangerous bicycle gang.
title: Velo Gang

overview: In Greek mythology, there were colossal creatures with fifty heads and a hundred arms. In the manner of an illustration in a bestiary, this short film describes the titan in a contemporary city. The concrete masses on the outskirts of Mexico City are the current version of the giant, recorded through 16mm film.
title: Hecatoncheires

overview: PREDATORS is a short dark, suburban slice-of-life tale, a paranoid character study of the dark-side of childhood. A group of kids lives are irrevocably changed when they discover a dangerous predator living in the woods.
tagline: A group of kids lives are irrevocably changed  when they discover a dangerous predator  living in the woods.
title: Predators

overview: While moving house, a middle-aged Muslim woman finds a box of old tapes filled with the memories of her husband's previous relationship and becomes increasingly obsessed.
title: Now and Then

overview: A skilled killer named Shui is forced to retire after a failed mission. He moves into an apartment arranged by the organization. However, unexpected murders start happening in the community. Shui decides to investigate and discovers that the community is concealing a conspiracy — there are hidden killers carrying out missions. Trapped in a dangerous situation, Shui’s only recourse comes from his ordinary neighbors.
title: Killers Never Old

overview: She Creates Change tells the true story of young Diksha from Nepal who overcame discrimination and went on to challenge unjust traditions in her community. She Creates Change film series was created for Room to Read NGO, will be released in October 2023 to commemorate International Day of the Girl, aims to reach all 432 million adolescent girls globally with content and educational curriculum that supports them in creating change in their communities.
title: She Creates Change: Diksha

overview: Sanae, who went to prison after failing to kill her ex-boyfriend six years ago, meets Kenta, a forest ranger, and gets married. Sanae and Kenta's married life takes a new turn when the wife of Sanae's ex-boyfriend appears. Sanae still can't forget her ex-boyfriend, and Kenta is having a hard time dealing with her.
title: After the Fever

overview: Farhan and Titi are a director-actor couple living in Dhaka. In a conservative and patriarchal Muslim society, they are criticized for not having children even after 10 years of marriage. As work decreases during the pandemic, Titi decides that now is a good time to have a child. She persuades Farhan and eventually succeeds in getting pregnant.
title: Something Like an Autobiography

overview: Jinhyeon, a social worker, learns that Yeongjin, a social service personnel in his charge, has been kicked out of his house and is living on the streets, so he allows him to stay at his house. Meanwhile, Sunrye, an elderly woman who visits the welfare center, complains to Jinhyeon too often.
title: Heritage

original_title: That They May Face the Rising Sun
overview: Joe and Kate Ruttledge have returned from London to live and work among the small, close-knit community near to where Joe grew up. Now deeply embedded in life around the lake, the drama of a year in their lives and those of the memorable characters around them unfolds through the rituals of work, play and the passing seasons as this enclosed world becomes an everywhere.
title: That They May Face the Rising Sun

overview: Imagining a revolutionary play authored by two female activists in the anti-colonial movement in post-war London.
title: A Radical Duet

original_title: Everything Worthwhile is Done with Other People
overview: Drawn from Zaman’s five-year collaboration with a group of Black and Global Majority women affected by incarceration, this engaging work interrogates the intersections of structural racism, classism and misogyny.
title: Everything Worthwhile is Done with Other People

overview: Different encounters as experienced by the indigenous population of Australia’s Northern Territory frame the narrative, enriched by the collective’s approach to filmic ‘world-making’.
title: Night Fishing with Ancestors

overview: As an esoteric, Soviet-era self-improvement practice, coding involves following instructions from a mysterious advisor – mind like a computer, programmable.
title: Coders

overview: Natural lifecycles, the labour of scavengers pouring over carrion, perform counterpoint to outsourced ghost tales from a Mechanical Turk platform.
title: Platform Ghosts – Turker, Farmer, Bot

original_title: Timekeepers of the Anthropocene: Tewame Tiyolicha Kawitl
overview: A message from interdimensional Nahua travellers is delivered across time, space and imposed borders, centring indigenous flourishing and resilience.
title: Timekeepers of the Anthropocene: Tewame Tiyolicha Kawitl

overview: Two figures in an idiosyncratic restorative session place grief onto a stone, alongside verbal self-soothing, guided gestures and blue thoughts.
title: TristxtOTL

overview: Rooted in Filipino realities – both concrete and cinematically reimagined – John Torres’ meticulous yet generous approach is a synthesis of the personal and the political. Assembling fragments of discordant images and murmuring voices, this inventive parable creates a present that appears alien and a future that feels familiar.
title: Room in a Crowd

overview: Over otherworldly 16mm images, we follow a mother’s haunting voice, recounting her day-to-day existence following the death of her daughter.
title: All the Days of May

overview: Finding parallels between a multi-generational, queer housing project and the study of old-growth forests, the film testifies to the ecological importance of diversity and care.
title: Wood for the Trees

overview: In rural Ghana, a young woman struggles with disruptive fits and growing jealously towards her best friend.
title: Doris

overview: A scientific experiment awakens violent impulses, in this striking stop motion horror.
title: The Test

overview: After years in Sweden, Malik finally moves back to Iraq, but he can’t shake the feeling of being an outsider.
title: Torn

overview: The loss of a family shop leads a young British Caribbean girl to consider her identity and sense of home.
title: South Facing

overview: A classical violinist and a drug dealer connect in a queer love story set on the streets of Bradford.
title: All the Lights Still Burning

overview: A Nigerian mother slaps her son so hard his life flashes before his eyes, in this humorous dissection of cultural stereotypes.
title: Festival of Slaps

overview: Tall tales from Brexit Britain run riot in this deadpan pool hall comedy.
title: Smoking Dolphins

overview: David's wife suddenly passes away. What follows is a quiet meditation on the family home being changed forever.
title: Mother of Mine

overview: French exchange student Gorka's UK stay takes an unexpected turn when he accompanies a British family on a poignant journey.
title: Gorka

overview: Who would dare hunt the desert guardian?
title: Ahru

overview: A young employee in the human resources team responsible for restructuring falls into emotional distress and conflict due to the work he has to do.
title: Work to Do

overview: Dong-chun, an elementary school student overwhelmed with seven afterschool learning academies, stumbles upon a mysterious bottle of rice wine during a school retreat. As the rice wine ferments and emits strange sounds like Morse code, Dong-chun sets out to unravel its identity and discovers the secrets of the world and the reasons behind her current way of life.
title: FAQ

overview: An ingenious performance play and docu-fiction about a group of artists in the near future facing the end of the world to prevent the apocalypse.
title: Sorigouldari: The Sound Underpass

overview: Three people pretend to be a family in order to solve their housing problem.
title: The Berefts

overview: Lala tells her friend Souad that she's determined to find herself a husband, as it's her grandmother's dream to attend her wedding. But what does she really want? Does she know?
title: Et toi, tu veux quoi?

overview: Watercolors is an omnibus documentary that highlights indie musicians who are seeking new paths and creating their own musical world.
title: Watercolors

overview: This story begins with a photo taken a century ago during the colonial era. The director goes to Yeongdeungpo with a camera to find any trace or signs of factory girls in the photo. There are no large factories anymore, only apartments, department stores, racetracks, inns, steel factories, restaurants, unidentified places, or empty ruins. Through the lives and landscapes of Yeongdeungpo, the director wants to discover any traces that factory girls might have left.
title: The Night of the Factory Girls

overview: Director Park Soo-nam, a second-generation Korean resident in Japan who is losing his eyesight, decides to digitally restore 16mm film she shot a long time ago, relying on her daughter Park Ma-eui's eyesight. The blood, tears, and numerous corpses of Koreans living in Japan are clearly engraved in the film filmed over 50 years.
title: The Voices of the Silenced

overview: In the midst of their parents' separation, sisters Cindy and Jena are forced to choose between which parent to go with, and consider the consequences of each choice.
title: The Rootless Bloom

overview: Aoqi and his girlfriend Qing Keer are about to part. An embarrassing incident happened between them and Aoqi's good friend Cha Ligan while parting.
title: Lamb Lamb Lamb

overview: While the post-war country is torn apart by the atmosphere of pessimism and suspense, 25-year-old Satenik has to watch videos of tortured war captives to help find soldiers gone missing during the war. Amongst them is Satenik’s brother.
title: Headless Horsemen

overview: As Sridhar prepares for his coming-of-age celebration, his grandfather tells him a shocking story about his family. As he pushes for the truth, his mother is caught in a dilemma between wanting to protect him and wanting to be honest.
title: The Witness Tree

overview: Deok-hee often ruins relationships by being excessively direct. Today, once again, P pushes her away.
title: She Wants True Love

overview: In 2027, Ga-eul, a hearing-impaired college student, learns about the app MYDEAR and becomes immersed in conversations with an AI presence. The app’s features easily help her overcome her disability, and the AI is affectionate and considerate, like a boyfriend.
title: MYDEAR

overview: Bong-sik dies after committing a heinous crime. Yet, even before the god of the underworld, he remains unrepentant and earns a hundred years of the severest punishment. Now, a hundred years later, Bong-sik receives a new karma, according to the rules of the underworld.
title: KARMA

overview: Na-eun and Yeon-su live together in a small room. For two hours a day, Yeon-su becomes invisible.
title: New Morning of an Artificial World

overview: Even before Yeon-ju finishes unpacking, her older sister Seon-ju unexpectedly barges into the cramped room, not large enough for the household items, and old possessions that fill it.
title: Flavor of Sisterhood

original_title: 초면에 발생한 분쟁을 조정하는 세 가지 질문
overview: Two strangers have an argument in an empty field in the early morning. When the argument escalates, the two are sent to the First-Encounter Dispute Resolution Committee, where they are asked three questions.
title: Three Questions That Lead to Love

overview: Fifteen-year-old So-min is upset that her family has to move after her father’s business flops. Her family arrives at their new home, but even before their possessions are unloaded, So-min and her younger brother head to their old home.
title: Home

overview: Between affections and tensions, the couple Marcela and Camila relate to the daily life of their suburban roots.
title: Ficção Suburbana

overview: The grim news made international headlines: On August 21, 1971, prison authorities discovered a gun on famed Soledad Brother author, activist and San Quentin inmate George Jackson. A shootout ensued, killing Jackson, two other inmates and three guards, and wounding three more officers. Authorities asserted that only lawyer Stephen Bingham could have smuggled the weapon into the prison. Fearing that a conviction for abetting the guards’ deaths would lead to his own murder, the attorney fled, beginning a long, strange odyssey of pseudonymous exile. Strange indeed for the Yale-graduate scion of politically prominent New England elites.
title: A Double Life

overview: The newly separated Leonor comes from the monied class, while sixteen year old aspiring ballerina Emilia does not. They begin a tense pas de deux waiting out Emilia’s pregnancy in a remote country home, isolated from the world and each other.
title: Heartbeat

overview: When Ollie’s mother is attacked by a monster hiding in the depths of Lake Merritt, he sets out on a mission to find her—discovering instead a hidden network of monster-hunters tasked with protecting Oakland from its own dark underbelly.
title: The Lake Merritt Monster

original_title: O Diabo na Rua no Meio do Redemunho
overview: The film is narrated by Riobaldo, who takes us into his life as a gunman and shares his experiences and conflicts. Throughout the plot, he becomes involved with several charismatic groups and leaders, including the feared Hermógenes. Riobaldo's heart is won by Diadorim, a brave and mysterious young man who becomes the love of his life. Through Riobaldo's narrative, the author explores the complexities of the human soul, delving into the duality between good and evil. Adaptation of the acclaimed masterpiece "Grande Sertão: Veredas", written by Guimarães Rosa.
title: The Devil to Pay in the Backlands

overview: Hélène returns to her native village under a new identity. Looking for revenge and, alone, she is ready to do anything to destroy the Graff family.
title: The Last Ashes

overview: An aspiring teen filmmaker casts the perfect lead for his breakout zombie film: his undead dad.
title: All You Need Is Blood

overview: WELCOME SPACE BROTHERS unveils the true story of The Unarius Academy of Science, a long-running extraterrestrial-channeling spiritual school in El Cajon, California that in the late 1970s became a wildly prolific filmmaking and art collective under the direction of outlandish spiritual leader and visionary filmmaker Ruth E. Norman, AKA “Archangel Uriel.”
title: Welcome Space Brothers

overview: A quirky comedy in which mythology, ancient history, and the sometimes paranormal present are never distinct, but always entertaining.
title: Lost on Kythera

overview: Kevin Jerome Everson’s unique observational gaze collapses Hollywood histrionics and American carceral history into one frame, as a Moscow prison break scene from Andrew Marlowe’s original screenplay for Air Force One—read in affectless voiceover on the film’s soundtrack—is offset by handheld footage taken in the Ohio State Reformatory, where the scene was filmed.
title: Air Force Two

overview: Titled after the United States Federal Court decree that forced the closure of the infamously overcrowded Ohio State Reformatory, Everson’s film is a radical transformation of the prison and popular filming location, at once abstracting its interiors into monochrome patterns and textures, and reanimating the ghostly traces of its real and fictive former inhabitants.
title: Boyd v. Denton

overview: A working-class drifter takes a road trip to reunite with his old friends at a cabin. While traveling, he encounters other souls populating the highways of a changing America. When he arrives, he finds his friends somewhat changed as well.
title: Berman's March

overview: Adrià is a boy who lives from village to village with his older brother and his older brother's girlfriend. He is mute, can't stand enclosed spaces, and finds it hard to keep his attention when spoken to. Adrià has a secret: on full moon nights, he can't sleep and wanders the streets.
title: Werewolf

overview: Narrated by Debbie Allen, the film bridges inspiring stories of individuals who have found purpose in their lives with the insights of leading scientists whose work affirms that living with purpose improves health and longevity.
title: The Hidden Power of Purpose

overview: A company promises a surefire system for becoming an influencer with millions of followers, but fame comes at a price.
title: Starr

overview: In the short span of half a century after World War II, the remote island of Kinmen has witnessed numerous battles. Its people once supported the national army, enduring the battles and gunfire. Today, memories have faded, and those who personally experienced the fires of war, the Kinmen residents who walked through fearful and sorrowful times, are gradually passing away. For the post-war new generation, the memories of billowing smoke may be fading, but the island's shadows have never disappeared.
title: No

overview: The Coco guesthouse cultivates new relationships, providing a platform for confronting personal pasts and futures.
title: Push Pause

overview: Three actors audition to play the Palestinian-Jewish actor and activist Juliano Mer-Khamis, a former IDF paratrooper who defiantly identified as “100% Palestinian and 100% Jewish”. During a tense rehearsal meant to determine which of them is most suited to authentically portray Juliano Mer-Khamis, the three Julianos find their sense-of-self fractured and disrupted.
title: Yes Repeat No

original_title: Al pasar: Cartas desde el trópico
overview: A film correspondence between a filmmaker, the ghost of an artist, and the city of Guayaquil.
title: Al pasar: Cartas desde el trópico

overview: Amado cut down twenty-five trees a day during the seven years he was a feller. Yadira grew up believing that as a woman, her possibilities were restricted to the home, but her desire was to be independent. They both live in the province of Esmeraldas, near the Canandé River in the Ecuadorian Chocó lowlands. Despite living in a reality where sources of work are mainly extractive, both have found ways to conserve the jungle in which they live.
title: While there is still jungle left

overview: “Telsche” is a 2D short animation film that explores memory, loss, and love. It is about the journey that one girl takes to remember someone she has long forgotten.
title: Telshe

overview: Documentary 5 chapter celebrating the 20th anniversary of "My Girl"
title: Remembering Fan Chan

original_title: Das Coisas que nos Pertencem e Deixamos para Trás
title: Das Coisas que nos Pertencem e Deixamos para Trás

titles.title: From The Things that Belongs to Us and We Left Behind

overview: Ania and Bartek, two stuttering teenagers undergoing speech therapy, are learning to like themselves and stop being afraid.
title: Echo

overview: The story of a boy who really wants to be stroked by his Mommy. Unfortunately, the woman's attention is completely focused on her beloved dog. What is the boy capable of to get his Mommy's attention…?
title: How to Be Loved?

overview: A man in emotional turmoil after a break-up seeks the advice of an imaginary figure to solve a missing person case.
title: Moonamghattam

overview: In a retirement home in a small village in the south of France, residents try to build a community. What ties can they still manage to forge in this anonymous environment often perceived as hostile?
title: Empty Hours

overview: Instead of devoting attention to his wife, a man concentrates all his love on his vegetable garden. One day all his delicious tomatoes mysteriously disappear.
title: Paumo D'amour

overview: A short animated documentary exploring the immigration experience through the eyes of a little Israeli girl learning how to swim with clothes on in the Netherlands.
title: Swimming with Wings

overview: A dark creature haunts Oscar as he mourns the recent death of his girlfriend.
title: Dogman

overview: One sunny day at the park was embraced by the multitude number of flowers of all shapes and colors. Sadly, a rainstorm suddenly glooms onto the park.
title: The Weather Within
